883
01:02:32,360 --> 01:02:34,720
And yeah, it is actually fantastic.

884
01:02:34,720 --> 01:02:39,180
So I think I might just have been hungry when I read the first issue back when I did.

885
01:02:39,560 --> 01:02:41,480
But it is a book.

886
01:02:41,480 --> 01:02:44,320
It's effectively role-playing game Jumanji.

887
01:02:44,320 --> 01:02:47,820
It's a group of six kids who are pulled into a role-playing game when they start playing.

888
01:02:47,820 --> 01:02:52,440
And then sort of a few years later, five of them come back out of the role-playing game.

889
01:02:53,040 --> 01:02:56,680
And there are some news stories saying, you know, where have they been?

890
01:02:56,680 --> 01:02:57,420
Where have they gone?

891
01:02:57,420 --> 01:02:57,900
Etc.

892
01:02:57,900 --> 01:03:03,860
And then they reunite as adults and they end up getting sucked back into the game.

893
01:03:03,860 --> 01:03:05,460
And it's the story of that.

894
01:03:05,460 --> 01:03:20,300
And it's effectively all of your regrets about how your life turned out from what you thought it would be when you were 16 to what it actually is when you're in your mid-40s as a 20-part comic.

895
01:03:20,300 --> 01:03:24,180
Which is quite well done.

896
01:03:24,180 --> 01:03:26,860
And there are some really poignant bits.

897
01:03:27,200 --> 01:03:35,620
It's got Gillen's kind of trademark Gillen-ness, which isn't a good way of putting it.

898
01:03:35,620 --> 01:03:41,320
But like he's clearly thought very meticulously about how everything's going to work.

899
01:03:41,320 --> 01:03:43,040
And it's all mapped out very well.

900
01:03:43,040 --> 01:03:48,140
There's an awful lot of kind of pathos, I think.

901
01:03:48,140 --> 01:03:50,100
And I just really enjoyed it.

902
01:03:50,100 --> 01:03:54,860
The art also by Stephanie Hans is absolutely gorgeous.

903
01:03:55,480 --> 01:03:57,860
Very, very un-comic-like in many ways.

904
01:03:57,860 --> 01:04:01,480
It's all sort of beautifully painted with a limited colour palette.

905
01:04:01,480 --> 01:04:11,180
